feat(brand-store): single Card Banner Image, drop Card Appearance, category dropdown picker

Per UX feedback, three changes to the admin brand edit + brand portal settings pages:

1. Showcase Images grid (max 5) collapsed into a single "Card Banner Image" upload.
   Schema unchanged (Brand.showcaseImages still String[]) — only the first
   element is used and rendered. Existing data with multiple images keeps
   working; only the first shows on the brand card.

2. Card Appearance section removed from both pages. bgColor still in schema
   (kept in form payload for backward compat) but no UI — brands now just
   get the green theme default.

3. Categories: free-text "type and Enter" input replaced with
   CategoryMultiPicker — searchable dropdown of existing admin-managed
   categories (loaded from /api/v1/categories). When a brand needs a
   category that does not exist, they type it in the search and tap
   "Request" — submitted to admin via new endpoint
   POST /api/v1/brand/categories/suggest (mirrors vendor suggest flow,
   creates Category with status=pending so admin reviews at /admin/categories).
   Admin context on /admin/brands/[id] uses /api/v1/admin/categories
   (auto-approved create).

New files:
- src/components/features/brand/CategoryMultiPicker.tsx — reusable picker
- src/app/api/v1/brand/categories/suggest/route.ts — brand-side suggest endpoint

